         <abstract>
            <p>Over the last decade, Brigham Young University has developed over a dozen interactive videodisc programs for personalized foreign language instruction. From the early prototypal projects to the current HyperCard and Toolbook packages, each of these programs has explored a different emphasis in interactivity. This article is a broad description of these different models, their variations and their implementation.</p>
         </abstract>
